Description: An R package wrapping the tidymodels classification pipeline from
    self-study 1. Provides a single entry point, ml_compare(), that splits data,
    pre-processes it, tunes three model families (Random Forest, Elastic Net
    logistic regression, XGBoost) via cross-validated grid search, selects the
    best model by ROC AUC, and evaluates it on a held-out test set. Results are
    returned as an S3 object of class 'mlstudy_result' with print, summary, and
    plot methods.
